'''José Ángel Córdoba Chambers''' (born 3 June 2001) is a Panamanian professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[defender (association football)|defender]] for {{English football updater|NorwichC}} club [[Norwich City F.C.|Norwich City]] and the [[Panama national football team|Panama national team]].

==Club career==
Córdoba started in the youth ranks and began his professional football career at [[C.A. Independiente de La Chorrera|Independiente de La Chorrera]]. In 2020 he was transferred to Spanish club [[Celta Vigo]], but did not manage to break through in the senior team and made appearances mainly with the reserve team.

In 2020, he went on a trial with Bulgarian side [[SFC Etar Veliko Tarnovo|Etar Veliko Tarnovo]]. Córdoba had a second trial with Etar before head coach [[Aleksandar Tomash]] decided to sign him on a permanent contract.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://topsport.bg/levski/koy-e-hose-kordoba-i-zashto-be-tolkova-zhelan-ot-levski.html|title=Кой е Хосе Кордоба и защо бе толкова желан от Левски?|language=bg|website=Topsport.bg|date=6 September 2021|access-date=6 September 2021}}</ref> Córdoba made ten appearances in the Bulgarian First League during the second half of the [[2020–21 First Professional Football League (Bulgaria)|2020–21 season]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://sportal.bg/football/player-232508|title=Хосе Кордоба (профил)|website=sportal.bg|language=bg|date=|access-date=}}</ref> The club however got relegated, but Córdoba decided to stay with Etar in the [[Second Professional Football League (Bulgaria)|Second League]] and appeared in eight more games before being loaned to [[PFC Levski Sofia|Levski Sofia]] for one year with option to buy in September 2021.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://levski.bg/%d0%bb%d0%b5%d0%b2%d1%81%d0%ba%d0%b8-%d0%bf%d0%be%d0%b4%d0%bf%d0%b8%d1%81%d0%b0-%d1%81-%d1%85%d0%be%d1%81%d0%b5-%d0%ba%d0%be%d1%80%d0%b4%d0%be%d0%b1%d0%b0/|title=Левски подписа с Хосе Кордоба|website=levski.bg|date=7 September 2021|access-date=7 September 2021|language=bg}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://etarvt.bg/2021/09/07/hose-kordoba-preminava-v-levski/|title=Хосе Кордоба преминава в "Левски"|website=etarvt.bg|date=7 September 2021|access-date=7 September 2021|language=bg}}</ref> On 5 April 2022, he signed with Levski on a permanent deal until 2025, coming into effect on 1 July 2022.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://levski.bg/%d0%bf%d1%84%d0%ba-%d0%bb%d0%b5%d0%b2%d1%81%d0%ba%d0%b8-%d0%bf%d0%be%d0%b4%d0%bf%d0%b8%d1%81%d0%b0-%d0%bd%d0%be%d0%b2-%d0%b4%d0%be%d0%b3%d0%be%d0%b2%d0%be%d1%80-%d1%81-%d1%85%d0%be/|title=Левски подписа нов договор с Хосе Кордоба|website=levski.bg|date=5 April 2022|access-date=5 April 2022|language=bg}}</ref>

On 5 June 2024, Córdoba was transferred to [[EFL Championship]] club [[Norwich City F.C.|Norwich City]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://levski.bg/%d0%bf%d1%84%d0%ba-%d0%bb%d0%b5%d0%b2%d1%81%d0%ba%d0%b8-%d1%82%d1%80%d0%b0%d0%bd%d1%81%d1%84%d0%b5%d1%80%d0%b8%d1%80%d0%b0-%d1%85%d0%be%d1%81%d0%b5-%d0%ba%d0%be%d1%80%d0%b4%d0%be/|title=Левски трансферира Хосе Кордоба|website=levski.bg|date=5 June 2024|access-date=7 June 2024|language=bg}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.canaries.co.uk/content/city-agrees-to-sign-jose-cordoba|title=City agree to sign José Córdoba|website=canaries.co.uk|date=6 June 2024|access-date=7 June 2024}}</ref> His first full league start was in a 4–1 home victory against [[Watford F.C.|Watford]]<ref>{{cite web|url= https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/live/cdx9ywq65zlt|title= Thorup gets first home league win as Norwich boss|website=BBC Sport|date= 21 Sep 2024|access-date=26 Sep 2024}}</ref> and he scored his first goal for the club in a defeat against [[Burnley F.C.|Burnley]] at [[Carrow Road]] on 15 December.<ref>{{cite web |title=Norwich 1 Burnley 2 |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/live/ckgx5x1y54qt |website=BBC Sport |access-date=23 December 2024}}</ref>

==International career==
In March 2022 Cordoba got his first call-up for the national team of Panama for the [[2022 FIFA World Cup qualification – CONCACAF third round|2022 FIFA World Cup qualification]] matches against [[Honduras national football team|Honduras]], [[United States men's national soccer team|USA]] and [[Canada men's national soccer team|Canada]]. He made his debut in the final qualifier of the campaign against Canada, playing full 90 minutes in a 1–0 win.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.fifa.com/tournaments/mens/worldcup/qatar2022/qualifiers/concacaf/match-center/400180556|title=Panama NT vs. Canada NT 1:0, FIFA World Cup Qualifier|language=en|website=fifa.com|date=31 March 2022|access-date=31 March 2022}}</ref>

